-- 2) Expand + balance the doctor roster (existing five kept; six added across departments).
update staff_user set department = 'Pediatrics' where staff_code = 'DOCTOR-PEDS';
update staff_user set department = 'Orthopedics' where staff_code = 'DOCTOR-ORTHO';
on conflict (staff_code) do nothing;

-- Patient OR-1001 — Ankle sprain from sports (LOW, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Jordan Kim

- Ankle ligament sprain: RICE protocol; likely soft-tissue injury.
- Watch for: ankle pain, swelling.
- Suggested tests: Ankle X-ray if Ottawa criteria met.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Ankle ligament sprain (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Ankle ligament sprain (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '17401 minutes');

-- Patient GE-1002 — Routine medication refill (LOW, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Neha Sharma

- Stable chronic condition - refill: No acute concern; routine review.
- Watch for: medication refill.
- Suggested tests: BP measurement.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Stable chronic condition - refill (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Stable chronic condition - refill (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '5852 minutes');

-- Patient GE-1003 — Severe abdominal pain and vomiting (HIGH, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Sanjay Gupta

- Possible appendicitis: Surgical review if right-lower-quadrant tenderness persists.
- Watch for: abdominal pain, vomiting, fever.
- Suggested tests: Abdominal ultrasound, CBC, Urinalysis.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Possible appendicitis (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Possible appendicitis (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '6547 minutes');

-- Patient EM-1004 — Asthma attack with wheezing (HIGH, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Sofia Martinez

- Asthma exacerbation: Bronchodilator therapy; reassess response.
- Watch for: wheezing, shortness of breath, cough.
- Suggested tests: Peak flow, SpO2, Chest auscultation.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Asthma exacerbation (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Asthma exacerbation (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '38512 minutes');

-- Patient PE-1005 — High fever with lethargy (HIGH, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Priya Nair

- Pediatric febrile illness: Monitor hydration and temperature; watch for febrile seizure.
- Watch for: fever, lethargy, poor feeding.
- Suggested tests: CBC, CRP, Urine culture.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Pediatric febrile illness (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Pediatric febrile illness (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '21315 minutes');

-- Patient PE-1006 — Loose motions and dehydration (MEDIUM, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Ananya Reddy

- Acute gastroenteritis: Oral rehydration; escalate if signs of severe dehydration.
- Watch for: diarrhea, dehydration.
- Suggested tests: Stool routine, Serum electrolytes.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Acute gastroenteritis (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Acute gastroenteritis (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '29429 minutes');

-- Patient EM-1007 — Severe breathing distress with low oxygen (CRITICAL, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Sofia Martinez

- Acute respiratory distress: Start supplemental oxygen; watch for respiratory failure.
- Watch for: shortness of breath, low oxygen saturation, wheezing.
- Suggested tests: ABG, Chest X-ray, SpO2 monitoring.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Acute respiratory distress (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Acute respiratory distress (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '14874 minutes');

-- Patient EM-1008 — Migraine with nausea (MEDIUM, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Vikram Desai

- Migraine headache: Rule out secondary causes if red-flag features appear.
- Watch for: headache, nausea, photophobia.
- Suggested tests: Clinical assessment, BP measurement.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Migraine headache (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Migraine headache (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '10709 minutes');

-- Patient OR-1009 — Lower back pain (LOW, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Arjun Kapoor

- Mechanical low back pain: Analgesia and activity advice; imaging only if red flags.
- Watch for: back pain.
- Suggested tests: Clinical assessment.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Mechanical low back pain (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Mechanical low back pain (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '28944 minutes');

-- Patient OR-1010 — Wrist injury after a fall (MEDIUM, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Jordan Kim

- Possible distal radius fracture: Immobilize and elevate; analgesia as needed.
- Watch for: wrist pain, swelling.
- Suggested tests: Wrist X-ray (AP + lateral).

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Possible distal radius fracture (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Possible distal radius fracture (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '14767 minutes');

-- Patient GE-1011 — Persistent cough and mild fever (LOW, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Neha Sharma

- Upper respiratory tract infection: Symptomatic care; return if breathing worsens.
- Watch for: cough, mild fever.
- Suggested tests: Clinical assessment.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Upper respiratory tract infection (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Upper respiratory tract infection (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '12577 minutes');

-- Patient GE-1012 — High fever, body ache and rash (HIGH, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Sanjay Gupta

- Suspected dengue fever: Monitor platelets and hydration; dengue is seasonally prevalent locally.
- Watch for: high fever, body ache, headache, rash.
- Suggested tests: CBC with platelet count, NS1 antigen, Dengue serology.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Suspected dengue fever (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Suspected dengue fever (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '36486 minutes');

-- Patient EM-1013 — Deep laceration with bleeding (HIGH, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Anika Shah

- Laceration requiring repair: Apply pressure, assess depth and neurovascular status.
- Watch for: bleeding, wound.
- Suggested tests: Wound assessment, Tetanus status review.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Laceration requiring repair (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Laceration requiring repair (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '25115 minutes');

-- Patient EM-1014 — Sudden slurred speech and facial droop (CRITICAL, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Vikram Desai

- Possible acute stroke: Activate stroke pathway; document last-known-well time.
- Watch for: slurred speech, facial droop, weakness.
- Suggested tests: Non-contrast CT head, Blood glucose, NIHSS assessment.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Possible acute stroke (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Possible acute stroke (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '18052 minutes');

-- Patient EM-1015 — Palpitations and dizziness (MEDIUM, DISCHARGED) -> Dr. Mateo Rivera

- Possible arrhythmia: Continuous monitoring if palpitations recur.
- Watch for: palpitations, dizziness.
- Suggested tests: 12-lead ECG, Electrolytes, Thyroid panel.

Sources:
- [PubMed] Clinical overview of Possible arrhythmia (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)
- [ICMR] Indian clinical guidance on Possible arrhythmia (https://www.icmr.gov.in/)', now() - interval '19287 minutes');

